  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22. separate you—whether from their Church, by excommunication, or from their society; both hard to flesh and blood.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the Son of man's sake—Compare Mt 5:11, \"for My sake\"; and immediately before, \"for righteousness' sake\" (Lu 6:10). Christ thus binds up the cause of righteousness in the world with the reception of Himself.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
